  "instructions": [
    "Heat olive oil in a large tagine or Dutch oven over medium heat; sauté chopped onion, garlic, and grated ginger until fragrant, about 3 minutes.",
    "Stir in paprika, cumin, coriander, and cinnamon, cooking for another minute.",
    "Add sliced carrots, diced zucchini, and tomato paste, cooking until vegetables lightly brown, about 4 minutes.",
    "Pour in vegetable broth and bring to a gentle simmer; add cooked chickpeas and cashews, season with salt and pepper.",
    "Reduce heat to low and simmer, covered, for 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.",
    "While simmering, boil or poach eggs until the whites set but yolks remain runny, about 6 to 7 minutes.",
    "Remove the pot from heat; stir in lemon juice and chopped cilantro, adjust seasoning if needed.",
    "Serve the tagine hot, topped with a poached egg, and enjoy a comforting, energy-boosting meal."
  ],
